    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (71.34) anchoring the outfield as our highest-projected start. His matchup against Ryne Nelson is the primary catalyst; he benefits from a robust +14% boost due to dynamic platoon advantages, positioning him as a high-upside play for stolen base production. Joining him in the \"Strong\" tier is **Colt Keith** (65.83), who leverages a favorable encounter with Kumar Rocker, buoyed by a +7% platoon edge and the expectation of a high-value #3 spot in the lineup. Despite the rain risk, **Caleb Durbin** (62.04) remains a must-start; while his #9 position suppresses his score, the 19% SP skill advantage against Spencer Arrighetti and the slow delivery of the opposing starter present a prime environment to exploit his elite sprint speed for stolen base accumulation.\n\nManaging the volatility of our bench, **Chase Meidroth** (44.21) was the final man left out of the starting nine. While his floor is respectable, the combination of a daunting matchup against the high-skill Michael King and the lack of a locked-in lineup position led the optimizer to prioritize the more favorable matchup context offered by **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Josh Smith**. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Yordan Alvarez** (51.14); while he offers elite power potential, the combination of a tough matchup against Connelly Early and the lingering 33% rain risk makes his utility volatile. With **Christian Yelich** remaining sidelined on the IL, we will rely on the depth of our outfield corps\u2014specifically the platoon-heavy profiles of **Luke Raley** and **Pete Crow-Armstrong**\u2014to bridge the production gap. Keep a close watch on the official lineups, as any shifts in the batting orders for **Gary Sanchez** or **Trea Turner** could necessitate late-hour adjustments to our projected scoring.",
